script.name: plugin.gz.CmpClean.Main
script.sourceplaintext:
$PageID = 7021 set script command: 725_COMPLEX_CLEANER * $Version = get script version
* $DEBUG = 0 $CClean.Config = get global variable: name='GZ.CCLEAN.CONFIG' $XTC.enabled = get global variable: name='XTC.ENABLED'
$Version = $CClean.Config[0] $DEBUG = $CClean.Config[1] $PageID = $CClean.Config[2] $CCK.Ware.Array = $CClean.Config[7]
$dummy = $CClean.Config[3] if $dummy == null OR $dummy < 20 play sample 971 return null end
* 1 normal script msg * 2 find safe position $Logfile = $PageID
$Ship.X = $SecPosition[0] $Ship.Y = $SecPosition[1] $Ship.Z = $SecPosition[2] $Sector = $SecPosition[3] $Target.Player = get player tracking aim $Hubs.Found = 0
* 1 hub, 2 clear, 3 restore, 4 ver, 5 version * 6 north, 7 south, 8 east, 9 west, 10 up, 11 down, 12 crunch, 13 combine $Cmd1 = read text: page=$PageID id=51 $Cmd2 = read text: page=$PageID id=52 $Cmd3 = read text: page=$PageID id=53 $Cmd4 = read text: page=$PageID id=54 $Cmd5 = read text: page=$PageID id=55 $Cmd6 = read text: page=$PageID id=56 $Cmd7 = read text: page=$PageID id=57 $Cmd8 = read text: page=$PageID id=58 $Cmd9 = read text: page=$PageID id=59 $Cmd10 = read text: page=$PageID id=60 $Cmd11 = read text: page=$PageID id=61 $Cmd12 = read text: page=$PageID id=62 $Cmd13 = read text: page=$PageID id=63 $Cmd15.hide = read text: page=$PageID id=65 $Cmd16.fps = read text: page=$PageID id=66 $Cmd17.check = read text: page=$PageID id=67 $Cmd18.ignore = read text: page=$PageID id=68 $Cmd19.drop = read text: page=$PageID id=69 $Cmd20.Relocate = read text: page=$PageID id=70
if $DEBUG write to log file #$Logfile append=null printf: fmt='CC started on %s in sector %s. Target sector: %s. Player target: %s', [THIS], [SECTOR], $Sector, $Target.Player, null write to log file #$Logfile append=[TRUE] printf: fmt='Cmd given: -%s-, Options on file: -%s-%s-%s-%s-', $Command, $Cmd1, $Cmd2, $Cmd3, null end
do if $Command == $Cmd18.ignore goto label Command.Ignore do if $Command == $Cmd19.drop goto label Command.Drop do if $Command == $Cmd20.Relocate goto label Cmd.Relocate
* Get TARGET * For ALL other targeted commands the position replaces the HUB target argument if $Command == $Cmd1 OR $Command == $Cmd6 OR $Command == $Cmd7 OR $Command == $Cmd8 OR $Command == $Cmd9 OR $Command == $Cmd10 OR $Command == $Cmd11 $Target.Player = null * Check for hub in the TARGET sector $Stations = $Sector -> get player owned station array from sector $Dist.Low = 999999999
$Index = size of array $Stations while $Index > 0 dec $Index = $Target = $Stations[$Index] gosub Check.For.Hub if $Target -> get local variable: name='GZ.FACTORY.MODULE.HOLDER' $Modular.Factory = $Target end if $Is.Hub $Dist = $Target -> get distance to: position array=$SecPosition if $Dist < $Dist.Low $Dist.Low = $Dist $Target.Player = $Target end * Brent note: this moved from the 'if' block above to here, to fix * a bug with the player target sometimes not being used. inc $Hubs.Found = end end
$Target = $Target.Player end
* Get TARGET * 51 Move Hub to Position * This is the only cmd where 2 arguments - a hub and a position - are needed. * In order to reduce script arguments I use the player target as the 2nd. if $Command == $Cmd1 * If there IS only one hub, I don't need this.
if $Hubs.Found != 1 $Target = get player tracking aim gosub Check.For.Hub if not $Is.Hub * Complex hub, no aim = speak text: page=17 id=7901 priority=20 = speak text: page=13 id=4 priority=20 return null end end end
* Correct hub position if player placed it too far or too close to the Mod.Factory if $Command == $Cmd1 AND $Modular.Factory != null AND $Hubs.Found == 1 $Dist = $Modular.Factory -> get distance to: position array=$SecPosition $Fact.X = $Modular.Factory -> get x position $Fact.Y = $Modular.Factory -> get y position $Fact.Z = $Modular.Factory -> get z position
if $DEBUG write to log file #$Logfile append=[TRUE] printf: fmt='Player wants the hub here: %s', $SecPosition, 'lowering distance.', $Cmd2, $Cmd3, null $dummy = $Modular.Factory -> get position as array write to log file #$Logfile append=[TRUE] printf: fmt='Module Complex is here: %s', $dummy, 'lowering distance.', $Cmd2, $Cmd3, null end
$Index = null if $Dist > 19000 do if $DEBUG write to log file #$Logfile append=[TRUE] printf: fmt='Distance to existing Mod.Complex is %s. %s', $Dist, 'lowering distance.', $Cmd2, $Cmd3, null $Index = ( 19000 * 1000 ) / $Dist $Ship.X = $SecPosition[0] $Ship.Y = $SecPosition[1] $Ship.Z = $SecPosition[2] $Ship.X = ( ( $Ship.X - $Fact.X ) * $Index ) / 1000 + $Fact.X $Ship.Y = ( ( $Ship.Y - $Fact.Y ) * $Index ) / 1000 + $Fact.Y $Ship.Z = ( ( $Ship.Z - $Fact.Z ) * $Index ) / 1000 + $Fact.Z $SecPosition[0] = $Ship.X $SecPosition[1] = $Ship.Y $SecPosition[2] = $Ship.Z
else if $Dist < 7600 do if $DEBUG write to log file #$Logfile append=[TRUE] printf: fmt='Distance to existing Mod.Complex is %s. %s', $Dist, 'increasing distance.', $Cmd2, $Cmd3, null $Ship.X = $Fact.X - 4000 $Ship.Y = $Fact.Y - 6500 $Ship.Z = $Fact.Z $SecPosition[0] = $Ship.X $SecPosition[1] = $Ship.Y $SecPosition[2] = $Ship.Z end $Dist = $Modular.Factory -> get distance to: position array=$SecPosition do if $DEBUG write to log file #$Logfile append=[TRUE] printf: fmt='Distance to existing Mod.Complex is %s. %s', $Dist, 'now.', $Cmd2, $Cmd3, null
end
* Fly CC ship to target sector if $Sector != [SECTOR] @ = [THIS] -> call script !move.jumptosector : sector=$Sector should followers jump too=[TRUE] end
* Check if $Command == $Cmd17.check $CClean.Config[0] = null @ START $Null -> call script setup.plugin.gz.CmpClean : Mode=null Mod.Type=null return null end
* FPS if $Command == $Cmd16.fps @ $dummy = [THIS] -> call script lib.gz.get.fps : $Msg = sprintf: pageid=$PageID textid=207, $dummy, null, null, null, null @ = wait 1 ms send incoming message $Msg to player: display it=[TRUE] return null end
* HIDE - obsolete command if $Command == $Cmd15.hide * START $Null-> call script 'plugin.gz.CmpClean.hide' : Select.in.Comp=null Select.out.of.Comp=[TRUE] Position=$SecPosition return null end
* CLEAR - Player must be in the sector so objects have a SIZE atribute if $Command == $Cmd2 if not [THIS] -> is in same sector as [PLAYERSHIP] $dummy = sprintf: pageid=$PageID textid=202, $Version, null, null, null, null * Target outside comm range, New remote cmd can not be executed. = speak text: page=13 id=36 priority=20 = speak text: page=13 id=133 priority=20 @ = wait 1 ms send incoming message $dummy to player: display it=[TRUE] return null end end
* 51 Move Hub to Position * 56-61 rotate Hub - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - if $Command == $Cmd1 OR $Command == $Cmd6 OR $Command == $Cmd7 OR $Command == $Cmd8 OR $Command == $Cmd9 OR $Command == $Cmd10 OR $Command == $Cmd11
if $Command == $Cmd1 $Target ->set position: x=$Ship.X y=$Ship.Y z=$Ship.Z else if $Command == $Cmd6 $Target ->set rotation: alpha=32768 beta=0 gamma=0 else if $Command == $Cmd7 $Target ->set rotation: alpha=0 beta=0 gamma=0 else if $Command == $Cmd8 $Target ->set rotation: alpha=16384 beta=0 gamma=0 else if $Command == $Cmd9 $Target ->set rotation: alpha=49152 beta=0 gamma=0 else if $Command == $Cmd10 $Target ->set rotation: alpha=32768 beta=49152 gamma=0 else if $Command == $Cmd11 $Target ->set rotation: alpha=32768 beta=16384 gamma=0 end
* 62 Crunch / 63 Combine - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - else if $Command == $Cmd12 OR $Command == $Cmd13 goto label Crunch
* 52 clear sector - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - else if $Command == $Cmd2 $FindCommand = 'clear' $Ship.Name = [THIS] -> get name * [THIS]-> set local variable: name='gz.old.name' value=$Ship.Name * [THIS]-> begin task $PageID with script 'plugin.gz.CmpClean.Rename' and priority 0: arg1=null arg2=null arg3=null arg4=null arg5=null gosub Store.Object.Sizes
$Stations = [SECTOR] -> get player owned station array from sector skip if $Stations return null
gosub Evade.Planet if not $Safe.Position $dummy = sprintf: pageid=$PageID textid=203, $Version, null, null, null, null @ = wait 1 ms send incoming message $dummy to player: display it=[TRUE] @ = wait 1 ms return null end
$Index = size of array $Stations while $Index > 0 dec $Index = gosub Rename.Ship
$Check.Station = $Stations[$Index] do if [PLAYERSHIP] -> is docking allowed at $Check.Station continue do if $Check.Station -> get local variable: name='GZ.FACTORY.MODULE' continue do if $Check.Station -> get local variable: name='GZ.FACTORY.MODULE.HOLDER' continue
$Msg = $Check.Station -> get name $Dist = get substring of $Msg offset=0 length=5 if $Dist == 'Your ' $Dist = get substring of $Msg offset=5 length=100 $Check.Station ->set name to $Dist end
$Old.Position = array alloc: size=0 $dummy = $Check.Station -> get x position append $dummy to array $Old.Position $dummy = $Check.Station -> get y position append $dummy to array $Old.Position $dummy = $Check.Station -> get z position append $dummy to array $Old.Position
$dummy = $Check.Station -> get rot alpha append $dummy to array $Old.Position $dummy = $Check.Station -> get rot beta append $dummy to array $Old.Position $dummy = $Check.Station -> get rot gamma append $dummy to array $Old.Position $Check.Station ->set local variable: name='gz.old.position' value=$Old.Position
$Is.fat.bastard = $Check.Station -> get local variable: name='gz.station.size' skip if $Is.fat.bastard > 3000 $Is.fat.bastard = null @ $dummy = [THIS] -> call script plugin.gz.CmpClean.FindPos : X Hub=$Ship.X Y Hub=$Ship.Y Z Hub=$Ship.Z Actor=[THIS] Is a mine=$Is.fat.bastard Command=$FindCommand
if not $dummy * No position found $Msg = sprintf: pageid=$PageID textid=200, $Version, null, null, null, null @ = wait 1 ms send incoming message $Msg to player: display it=[TRUE] return null end $New.X = $dummy[0] $New.Y = $dummy[1] $New.Z = $dummy[2] @ = wait 100 ms do if ( $DEBUG AND 1 ) > 0 write to log file #$Logfile append=[TRUE] printf: fmt='Moving %s to %s, %s, %s', $Check.Station, $New.X, $New.Y, $New.Z, null $Check.Station ->set position: x=$New.X y=$New.Y z=$New.Z $Check.Station ->set rotation: alpha=0 beta=2500 gamma=1500 $Check.Station ->ignore collisions: [TRUE] end
* 53 restore fabs - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - * unconnected fabs only else if $Command == $Cmd3 $FindCommand = 'restore' $Ship.Name = [THIS] -> get name [THIS] ->set local variable: name='gz.old.name' value=$Ship.Name [THIS] ->start task $PageID with script plugin.gz.CmpClean.Rename and prio 0: arg1=null arg2=null arg3=null arg4=null arg5=null
$Stations = [SECTOR] -> get player owned station array from sector skip if $Stations return null $Index = size of array $Stations * $Target = get player tracking aim if $Target gosub Check.For.Hub end if $Is.Hub $Ship.X = $Target -> get x position $Ship.Y = $Target -> get y position $Ship.Z = $Target -> get z position else * $Ship.Y = $Ship.Y + 20000 end
while $Index > 0 dec $Index = * gosub Rename.Ship:
$Check.Station = $Stations[$Index]
skip if [PLAYERSHIP] -> is docking allowed at $Check.Station continue do if $Check.Station -> get local variable: name='GZ.FACTORY.MODULE' continue do if $Check.Station -> get local variable: name='GZ.FACTORY.MODULE.HOLDER' continue
$Target = $Check.Station gosub Check.For.Hub do if $Is.Hub continue
$Is.fat.bastard = $Check.Station -> get local variable: name='gz.station.size' skip if $Is.fat.bastard > 3000 $Is.fat.bastard = null @ $dummy = [THIS] -> call script plugin.gz.CmpClean.FindPos : X Hub=$Ship.X Y Hub=$Ship.Y Z Hub=$Ship.Z Actor=[THIS] Is a mine=$Is.fat.bastard Command=$FindCommand
if not $dummy * No position found $Msg = sprintf: pageid=$PageID textid=201, $Version, null, null, null, null @ = wait 1 ms send incoming message $Msg to player: display it=[TRUE] return null end $New.X = $dummy[0] $New.Y = $dummy[1] $New.Z = $dummy[2] @ = wait 100 ms $Check.Station ->set position: x=$New.X y=$New.Y z=$New.Z $Check.Station ->set rotation: alpha=0 beta=2500 gamma=1500 $Check.Station ->ignore collisions: [FALSE] do if ( $DEBUG AND 1 ) > 0 write to log file #$Logfile append=[TRUE] printf: fmt='Moving %s to %s, %s, %s', $Check.Station, $New.X, $New.Y, $New.Z, null end else * unknown command or Help $dummy = sprintf: pageid=$PageID textid=100, $Version, $Command, null, null, null @ = wait 1 ms send incoming message $dummy to player: display it=[TRUE] = speak text: page=13 id=135 priority=20 return null end * Complex Hub, Formation established = speak text: page=17 id=7901 priority=20 = speak text: page=13 id=35 priority=20 return null
* - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Check.For.Hub: $Is.Hub = null do if $Target -> is of class Complex Hub $Is.Hub = 1 * $Is.a.mine = null * do if $Target-> is of type {Argon Complex Hub} * $Is.Hub = 1 * do if $Target-> is of type {Boron Complex Hub} * $Is.Hub = 1 * do if $Target-> is of type {Paranid Complex Hub} * $Is.Hub = 1 * do if $Target-> is of type {Split Complex Hub} * $Is.Hub = 1 * do if $Target-> is of type {Teladi Complex Hub (FAC_T_COMPLEX)} * $Is.Hub = 1 endsub
* - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Store.Object.Sizes: $Stations = [SECTOR] -> get player owned station array from sector $Index = size of array $Stations
while $Index dec $Index = $Check.Station = $Stations[$Index] $dummy = $Check.Station -> get size of object $Check.Station ->set local variable: name='gz.station.size' value=$dummy end endsub
Rename.Ship: * $dummy = $Index + ' ' + $Ship.Name * [THIS]-> set name to $dummy * = wait 1 ms endsub
Evade.Planet: if ( $DEBUG AND 2 ) > 0 write to log file #$Logfile append=[TRUE] value=' ' write to log file #$Logfile append=[TRUE] value=[SECTOR] end $Test.Dummies = array alloc: size=0 $Test.Pos.X = array alloc: size=0 $Test.Pos.Z = array alloc: size=0
append 100000 to array $Test.Pos.X append -140000 to array $Test.Pos.X append 200000 to array $Test.Pos.X append -220000 to array $Test.Pos.X
append 100000 to array $Test.Pos.Z append -140000 to array $Test.Pos.Z append 200000 to array $Test.Pos.Z append -220000 to array $Test.Pos.Z
$dummy = array alloc: size=0 append 0 to array $dummy append 0 to array $dummy append 0 to array $dummy $Dist = get distance: position array1=$SecPosition array2=$dummy if $Dist > 99000 append $Ship.X to array $Test.Pos.X append $Ship.Z to array $Test.Pos.Z $Ship.Y = $SecPosition[1] do if ( $DEBUG AND 2 ) > 0 write to log file #$Logfile append=[TRUE] printf: fmt='Checking Player supplied position of %s, %s, %s.', $Ship.X, $Ship.Y, $Ship.Z, null, null else $Ship.Y = 50000 do if ( $DEBUG AND 2 ) > 0 write to log file #$Logfile append=[TRUE] printf: fmt='Player supplied position to close to center. Finding safe position.', null, null, null, null, null end
$Ind.X = size of array $Test.Pos.X while $Ind.X > 0 dec $Ind.X = $Ship.X = $Test.Pos.X[$Ind.X]
$Ind.Z = size of array $Test.Pos.Z while $Ind.Z > 0 dec $Ind.Z = $Ship.Z = $Test.Pos.Z[$Ind.Z]
gosub Lets.Try.This do if $Safe.Position endsub
end end endsub
Lets.Try.This: do if ( $DEBUG AND 2 ) > 0 write to log file #$Logfile append=[TRUE] printf: fmt='Checking Position %s, %s, %s', $Ship.X, $Ship.Y, $Ship.Z, null, null $Safe.Position = 1 resize array $Test.Dummies to 0 $Test.X = $Ship.X - 7000 while $Test.X < $Ship.X + 60000 $Test.X = $Test.X + 58000
$Test.Z = $Ship.Z - 7000 while $Test.Z < $Ship.Z + 60000 $Test.Z = $Test.Z + 58000
$Test.Y = $Ship.Y - 203000 while $Test.Y < $Ship.Y $Test.Y = $Test.Y + 100000 do if ( $DEBUG AND 2 ) > 0 write to log file #$Logfile append=[TRUE] printf: fmt=' Created dummy at %s, %s, %s', $Test.X, $Test.Y, $Test.Z, null, null
$Ship = create ship: type=Demeter Super Freighter XL owner=Neutral Race addto=[SECTOR] x=$Test.X y=$Test.Y z=$Test.Z append $Ship to array $Test.Dummies @ START $Ship -> call script plugin.gz.CmpClean.die : Die.Delay=33000 @ = wait 1 ms end end end * Survivability Test @ = wait 2000 ms @ = wait 1000 ms @ = wait 2000 ms
$Index = size of array $Test.Dummies do if ( $DEBUG AND 2 ) > 0 write to log file #$Logfile append=[TRUE] printf: fmt='%s dummies found', $Index, $Test.Y, $Test.Z, null, null
while $Index > 0 dec $Index = $Crash.Dummy = $Test.Dummies[$Index] skip if $Crash.Dummy -> exists $Safe.Position = null
$dummy = $Crash.Dummy -> get shield and hull percent do if ( $DEBUG AND 2 ) > 0 write to log file #$Logfile append=[TRUE] printf: fmt='%s : Hull Shield %s', $Index, $dummy, $Test.Z, null, null skip if $dummy == 100 $Safe.Position = null end do if ( $DEBUG AND 2 ) > 0 write to log file #$Logfile append=[TRUE] printf: fmt='Position safe: %s', $Safe.Position, $Test.Y, $Test.Z, null, null * $Safe.Position = null endsub
* - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Command.Ignore: $Target = get player tracking aim $Sector = [PLAYERSHIP] -> get sector $Test.Dummies = 'GZ.CCLEAN.IGNORE' $Ignore.Tag = read text: page=$PageID id=168
if $Target skip if $Target -> is of class Station $Target = null $dummy = $Target -> get owner race do if $dummy != Player $Target = null end
if $Target * Player owned station targeted. Toggle ignore. if $Target -> get local variable: name=$Test.Dummies $Target ->set local variable: name=$Test.Dummies value=null else $Target ->set local variable: name=$Test.Dummies value=[TRUE] end end
* ALWAYS : Show ignore flags for all stations $Stations = $Sector -> get player owned station array from sector $Index = size of array $Stations while $Index > 0 dec $Index = $Check.Station = $Stations[$Index] $dummy = $Check.Station -> get name $Has.Ignore.Tag = find position of pattern $Ignore.Tag in $dummy if $Has.Ignore.Tag > -1 $Has.Ignore.Tag = [TRUE] else $Has.Ignore.Tag = null end
if $Check.Station -> get local variable: name=$Test.Dummies * Station should have a tag if $Has.Ignore.Tag continue else $dummy = $dummy + $Ignore.Tag $Check.Station ->set name to $dummy continue end
else * Station should not have a tag if not $Has.Ignore.Tag continue else $dummy = substitute in string $dummy: pattern $Ignore.Tag with '' $Check.Station ->set name to $dummy continue end end end return null
* - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Crunch: * I wana make you crunch, crunch til you crunch no more $Index = 'x' $dummy = 'a' while $Index != $dummy $Station.Arr = $Sector -> get player owned station array from sector $Index = size of array $Station.Arr @ = $Null -> call script plugin.gz.CmpClean.crunch : Position=$SecPosition $Station.Arr = $Sector -> get player owned station array from sector $dummy = size of array $Station.Arr end return null
* - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Command.Drop: $Stations.built = 0 $Stations.not.built = 0 $Station.const.kits = 0 $Cargo.Class.ST = get ware from maintype 6 and subtype 1 $Cargo.Class.ST = get transport class of ware $Cargo.Class.ST $Planets.Arr = $Sector -> get planet array * $Station.Arr = create new array, arguments={Argon Complex Construction Kit}, {Boron Complex Construction Kit}, {Paranid Complex Construction Kit}, {Split Complex Construction Kit}, {Teladi Complex Construction Kit}
$Ships.Arr = $Sector -> get ship array from sector/ship/station $Index1 = size of array $Ships.Arr if $DEBUG write to log file #3424 append=[TRUE] printf: fmt=' ', 'CMD drop ', $Sector, null, null, null write to log file #3424 append=[TRUE] printf: fmt='%s, %s, %s, %s, %s', 'CMD drop ', $Sector, null, null, null end
while $Index1 dec $Index1 = $Ship = $Ships.Arr[$Index1] $Dummy1 = $Ship -> is hired $Dummy2 = $Ship -> get owner race if $Dummy2 == Player OR $Dummy1 != null $Dummy1 = $Ship -> get max. ware transport class do if $Dummy1 == $Cargo.Class.ST gosub Ship.Drop.Station end end
* Completion message here $dummy = sprintf: pageid=$PageID textid=401, $Sector, $Stations.built, $Stations.not.built, $Station.const.kits, null @ = wait 1 ms send incoming message $dummy to player: display it=[TRUE]
return null
* - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Ship.Drop.Station: do if $DEBUG write to log file #3424 append=[TRUE] printf: fmt='Drop stations: %s', $Ship, null, null, null, null
$Is.Hub = 6 $Index2 = get number of subtypes of maintype $Is.Hub while $Index2 dec $Index2 = $Ware = get ware from maintype $Is.Hub and subtype $Index2 do if $Ship -> get amount of ware $Ware in cargo bay gosub Check.and.build.station end
$Is.Hub = 5 $Index2 = get number of subtypes of maintype $Is.Hub while $Index2 dec $Index2 = $Ware = get ware from maintype $Is.Hub and subtype $Index2 do if $Ship -> get amount of ware $Ware in cargo bay gosub Check.and.build.station end endsub
* - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Check.and.build.station: $Ind.X = $Ship -> get amount of ware $Ware in cargo bay do if $DEBUG write to log file #3424 append=[TRUE] printf: fmt=' Amount: %s, MT: %s, ST: %s, %s', $Ind.X, $Is.Hub, $Index2, $Ware, null
if find $Ware in array: $CCK.Ware.Array $Station.const.kits = $Station.const.kits + $Ind.X endsub end
* Test factory do if $DEBUG write to log file #3424 append=[TRUE] printf: fmt=' Testing station: %s', $Ware, 6, $Index2, $Ware, null * Brent note: owner changed from neutral to player here, since when neutral * some factory types (eg. teladi medium SPP) do not initialize their wares * correctly, and end up getting ignored. $Stations = create station: type=$Ware owner=Player addto=$Sector x=100000 y=-120000 z=80000 $Stations ->add default wares to station/dock @ = wait 1 ms $Stations ->factory production task: on=[TRUE] @ = wait 1 ms $Dummy1 = $Stations -> get number of products per cycle do if $XTC.enabled $Dummy1 = 1 $Dummy2 = $Stations -> get product ware $Stations ->destruct: show no explosion=[TRUE] do if $Dummy2 == Ore OR $Dummy2 == Silicon Wafers OR $Dummy2 == Ice $Dummy2 = Ore @ = wait 1 ms
if $Dummy1 == 0 OR $Dummy2 == Ore $Stations.not.built = $Stations.not.built + $Ind.X
else do if $DEBUG write to log file #3424 append=[TRUE] printf: fmt=' Building Station: %s x %s', $Ind.X, $Ware, $Index2, $Ware, null
* Build stations: $Stations.built = $Stations.built + $Ind.X = $Ship -> add -99999999 units of $Ware while $Ind.X dec $Ind.X = gosub Find.Station.Pos $Stations = create station: type=$Ware owner=Player addto=$Sector x=$New.X y=$New.Y z=$New.Z $Stations ->add default wares to station/dock $Stations ->factory production task: on=[TRUE] @ = wait 1 ms end end endsub
* - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Find.Station.Pos: $Index3 = 25 while $Index3 dec $Index3 = $New.X = random value from -90000 to 90000 - 1 $New.Y = random value from 70000 to 140000 - 1 $New.Z = random value from -90000 to 90000 - 1 $Index4 = size of array $Planets.Arr while $Index4 > 0 dec $Index4 = $Dummy1 = $Planets.Arr[$Index4] $Dummy2 = $Dummy1 -> get distance to: x=$New.X y=$New.Y z=$New.Z do if $Dummy2 < 640000 $Index4 = -9 end do if $Index4 != -9 break end endsub
* - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Cmd.Relocate: $Station.Arr = $Sector -> get station array from sector $Index = size of array $Station.Arr while $Index dec $Index = $Check.Station = $Station.Arr[$Index] if $Check.Station -> get local variable: name='GZ.FACTORY.MODULE.HOLDER' $Check.Station ->set local variable: name='GZ.CC.FMH.POSITION' value=$SecPosition = speak text: page=13 id=34 priority=8 return null end
end = speak text: page=13 id=25 priority=8
return null

line.var: 'CC started on %s in sector %s. Target sector: %s. Player target: %s'

comment.var: For ALL other targeted commands the position replaces the HUB target argument
Check for hub in the TARGET sector

line.text: get player owned station array from sector

comment.var: Brent note: this moved from the 'if' block above to here, to fix
a bug with the player target sometimes not being used.
This is the only cmd where 2 arguments - a hub and a position - are needed.
In order to reduce script arguments I use the player target as the 2nd.
If there IS only one hub, I don't need this.
Correct hub position if player placed it too far or too close to the Mod.Factory
Fly CC ship to target sector
